3. Document Fragmentâ€Šâ€”â€Šcreates a virtual copy of a document, that can store multiple elements. By inserting document fragment into DOM, it becomes empty, and cause only oneÂ reflow;
4. Event delegation andÂ bubbling

When we emit an Event, ex. click, the event is bubbling up to <html> element through the parentElement link:

-html (bubble click)
   -body (bubble click)
        -div (bubble click)
            -p 
            -p (click)

Delegation is used to improve performance. Letâ€™s say we have a structure:

-div.parent
    -p.child 
    -p.child
    -p.child
And we want to assign an addEventListener toÂ .childÂ , in this case, we have to attach event to 3 elements. Instead, we can attach event only toÂ .parent and resolve theÂ logic.
document.querySelector(".parent").addEventListener("click", function(event) {
    if (event.target.classList.contains("child")) {
      // you logic is here
    };
});
